caption.title: Phylogenetic analyses of DENV-2 viruses in Taiwan, 2001–2003.
caption.p: Maximum-likelihood tree with bootstrap values was constructed from the 73 E gene (1485 nt), using 63 DENV-2 viruses and 10 other serotypes of DENVs isolated in Taiwan and other countries. The DENV-2 viruses causing the 2001–2003 epidemic belonged to cosmopolitan genotype A and clustered with Philippine strains.
